dialogue: Aight.
It's me, man, Pete Evans... Chickie Pete. How you doing?
Bingo.
Chickie Pete. You look good.
Damn. Shit man. Been ages! Beer? On me?
I got an early morning-
Naw naw man, you gotta let me buy you a beer.
...I mighta played professional, if things had been different.
You think so?
For sure, man, I used to...

... I coulda been in a funk band, an orch-est-ra! Ha. Haydn, Bach Vivaldi, backing up Miles... A doctor inventing shit that saves lives. I got ideas man. Nickel. Damn. You know, I still remember the periodic table of elements.
Huh?

It's how I got started cooking. You know one brotha dreamed that whole thing up. Dmitri Mendeleev or some shit. Ha. He also made that Russian vodka 40 proof. I'm not thankful for those times. That was a long time ago. My hands man.
I just spent 30 days drying out.
Oh...
It's okay I can handle it now. I always drank. Then it was like the more I tried to settle down, the more I got blotto every night. Couldn't sleep in the dark. Still can't sleep in the dark.

Last May I got into it with this guy, the judge says either jail or a program, no choice at all there. I'm living with my sister in Harlem. She's letting me stay while I figure out my next move. I've always liked it up there. But shit man, you know Chickie Pete gon' be awright. If it's one thing Nickel taught me, it's how not to die. Ha. What you up to?
I got a moving company, trucks, employees.
My man! Moving on up! You got a lady?
No. I mean, I did, but it didn't work out. "Denise." She said I had a lotta work to do on myself.
I hear you, I hear you. Hard to find somebody who could understand.
Yeah, I'm still looking for the "one". Maybe some day.
You seen any of the guys? I've ran into some over the years. Black Mike's a crook, Nelson's strung out, Desmond lost an arm in `Nam. Yeah. You got out in `67?
You don't remember?
Remember what?
You really don't remember?

What? Shit, I remember what they did to Griff. Sshhitt. What they did to me. When they stuffed that kid in the big dryer. And the one they made eat a lightbulb, ha. You know what I remember?! The effing ghost... man, slipping on skin, flesh, whatever the hell it was in the shower. Yeah. What else you want me to remember?
-Nothing. Time served. And they kicked me out. I went up to Atlanta and then trained it going north. You know, been here since `68. Twenty years.
Yeah, that's nice. Everybody's welcomed here... what happened to that kid you used to hang around with all the time?
Which kid?
The kid, you know- y'all thought that hiding place was so secret.
Hmm.
Gotta take a leak, it'll come back to me.
I got to go, man.
No no, I hear you, me too. I don't want to ask. But if you're looking for a hand, I could use the job. I'm sleeping on a couch.
Right.
You have a card?
Not on me.
I can handle the work, is what I'm putting out there.
You ring me up- for the old days.
I will.
